<setup>

<math name="a">2</math>
<math name="r1">3.5</math>  
<math name="r2">0.5</math> 
<math name="r3">4</math>   
<math name="c">-4</math>     
<!--  <selectFromSequence assignNames="a" from="1" to="4" step="1" numToSelect="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="r1" from="3.5" to="4.5" step="0.5" numToSelect="1"/>  
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="r2" from="0" to="1" step="0.5" numToSelect="1"/>    
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="r3" from="3.5" to="4.5" step="0.5" numToSelect="1"/> 
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="c" from="-4" to="-3" step="0.25" numToSelect="1"/> -->
  
  <function name="g" symbolic="false">-1*$a/100 * (x + $r1) * (x + $r2)^2 * (x - $r3)</function>
  <derivative name="gP" symbolic="false">$g</derivative>  
  <derivative name="gPP" symbolic="false">$gP</derivative>      
  <function name="L" symbolic="false" styleNumber="3" labelPosition="lowerRight">$$gP($A.x)(x-$A.x) + $$g($A.x)</function>  
    <point name="A" styleNumber="2" coords="(-3,$$g(3))" showCoordsWhenDragging="false" draggable="true" labelPosition="upperRight"> 
      <label><m>A</m></label>
      <constraints>
          <attractToGrid dx="0.5"/>
            <constrainTo>$g</constrainTo>
      </constraints>      
    </point> 

  <label name="gLabel" anchor="(3,$$g(3)+0.5)"><m>y = f(x)</m></label>
<!--  <label name="LLabel" anchor="(-3,$$L(-3)+0.25)"><m>y = L(x)</m></label> -->

    <line name="line1" styleNumber="5" through="(-1,-3) (1,-3)" />
    <point name="P1" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c,-3) </point>
    <label name="P1Label" anchor="($c,-3.4)"><m>x_1</m></label>

    <point name="P2" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c+1.5,-3) </point>
    <label name="P2Label" anchor="($c+1.5,-3.4)"><m>x_2</m></label>

      <point name="P3" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c+3,-3) </point>
    <label name="P3Label" anchor="($c+3,-3.4)"><m>x_3</m></label>

    <point name="P4" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c+4.5,-3) </point>
    <label name="P4Label" anchor="($c+4.5,-3.4)"><m>x_4</m></label>

    <point name="P5" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c+6,-3) </point>
    <label name="P5Label" anchor="($c+6,-3.4)"><m>x_5</m></label>

    <point name="P6" styleNumber="5" draggable="false">($c+7.5,-3) </point>
    <label name="P6Label" anchor="($c+7.5,-3.4)"><m>x_6</m></label>
  
 <lineSegment name="v1" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c,-3) ($c,$$g($c))" />
 <lineSegment name="v2" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c+1.5,-3) ($c+1.5,$$g($c+1.5))" />

   <lineSegment name="v3" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c+3,-3) ($c+3,$$g($c+3))" />
 <lineSegment name="v4" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c+4.5,-3) ($c+4.5,$$g($c+4.5))" />

   <lineSegment name="v5" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c+6,-3) ($c+6,$$g($c+6))" />
 <lineSegment name="v6" styleNumber="6" endpoints="($c+7.5,-3) ($c+7.5,$$g($c+7.5))" />
  
</setup>

  <p>Let <m>f</m> be the function given by the graph below and consider its tangent line at the point <m>A</m>, which you can adjust by dragging <m>A</m>.</p>

<!--  <p><m>a = $a</m>, <m>b = $b</m>, and <m>c = $c</m>, so <m>g(x) = $$g(x)</m> and <m>L(x) = $$L(x)</m>, plus <m>A = $A</m> and <m>B = $B</m></p> -->

    <figure>
      <graph xmin="-5" xmax="5" ymin="-5" ymax="4" size="medium" grid="false" showNavigation="false" displayXAxis="false" displayYAxis="false"> $g $L $A $gLabel $line1 $P1 $P1Label $P2 $P2Label $P3 $P3Label $P4 $P4Label $P5 $P5Label  $P6 $P6Label $v1 $v2 $v3 $v4 $v5 $v6
      </graph>
      <caption>Plot of <m>y = f(x)</m> and its tangent line at the point <m>A</m></caption>
    </figure>

<!--
<p> <m>f(<math>$P1.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P1.x)</math> </m>, <m>f(<math>$P2.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P2.x)</math> </m>, <m>f(<math>$P3.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P3.x)</math> </m>, 
<m>f(<math>$P4.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P4.x)</math> </m>, <m>f(<math>$P5.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P5.x)</math> </m>, <m>f(<math>$P6.x</math>) = <math>$$g($P6.x)</math> </m>, </p> 

<p> <m>f'(<math>$P1.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P1.x)</math> </m>, <m>f'(<math>$P2.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P2.x)</math> </m>, <m>f'(<math>$P3.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P3.x)</math> </m>, 
<m>f'(<math>$P4.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P4.x)</math> </m>, <m>f'(<math>$P5.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P5.x)</math> </m>, <m>f'(<math>$P6.x</math>) = <math>$$gP($P6.x)</math> </m>, </p>
-->



 <ol marker="a.">
  <li>
    <p>At which location among <m>x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_6</m> is <m>f(x)</m> greatest?  (If you think the result is <m>x_3</m>, enter <q>x3</q>.) <answer>x5</answer>.</p>
  </li>  
  <li>
    <p>At which of <m>x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_6</m> is <m>f(x)</m> least?   <answer>x1</answer>.</p>
  </li> 
  <li> 
    <p>At which of <m>x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_6</m> is <m>f'(x)</m> greatest?  <answer>x1</answer>.</p>
  </li>  
  <li>
    <p>At which of <m>x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_6</m> is <m>f'(x)</m> least?   <answer>x6</answer>.</p>
  </li> 
  <li>
    <p>At which of <m>x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_6</m> is <m>f'(x)</m> closest to 0?   <answer>x2</answer>.</p>
  </li>      
 </ol>  

